com.pkrete.xrd4j.client

Interface SOAPClient

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SOAPClientImpl

    public interface SOAPClient
    This class defines an interface for SOAP client that can be used for sending SOAPMessage and ServiceRequest objects to SOAP endpoints.

    • Method Detail

      • send

        SOAPMessage send(SOAPMessage request,
               String url)
                 throws SOAPException,
                        MalformedURLException
        Sends the given message to the specified endpoint and blocks until it has returned the response. Null is returned if the given url is malformed or if sending the message fails.
        Parameters:
        request - the SOAPMessage object to be sent
        url - URL that identifies where the message should be sent
        Returns:
        the SOAPMessage object that is the response to the request message that was sent.
        Throws:
        SOAPException - if there's a SOAP error
        MalformedURLException - if no protocol is specified, or an unknown protocol is found, or url is null

      • send

        ServiceResponse send(ServiceRequest request,
                   String url,
                   ServiceRequestSerializer serializer,
                   ServiceResponseDeserializer deserializer)
                     throws SOAPException,
                            MalformedURLException
        Sends the given message to the specified endpoint and blocks until it has returned the response. Null is returned if the given url is malformed or if sending the message fails. Serialization and deserialization from/to SOAPMessage is done inside the method.
        Parameters:
        request - the ServiceRequest object to be sent
        url - URL that identifies where the message should be sent
        serializer - the ServiceRequestSerializer object that serializes the request to SOAPMessage
        deserializer - the ServiceResponseDeserializer object that deserializes SOAPMessage response to ServiceResponse
        Returns:
        the ServiceResponse object that is the response to the message that was sent.
        Throws:
        SOAPException - if there's a SOAP error
        MalformedURLException - if no protocol is specified, or an unknown protocol is found, or url is null

      • listClients

        List<ConsumerMember> listClients(String url)
        Calls listClients meta service and retrieves list of all the potential service providers (i.e., members and subsystems) of an X-Road instance. Returns a list of list of ConsumerMembers that represent X-Road clients.
        Parameters:
        url - URL of X-Road security server
        Returns:
        list of ConsumerMembers

      • listCentralServices

        List<ProducerMember> listCentralServices(String url)
        Calls listCentralServices meta service and retrieves list of all central services defined in an X-Road instance. Returns a list of ProducerMembers that represent X-Road central services.
        Parameters:
        url - URL of X-Road security server
        Returns:
        list of ProducerMembers

      • listMethods

        ServiceResponse listMethods(ServiceRequest request,
                          String url)
                            throws SOAPException,
                                   MalformedURLException
        Calls listMethods meta service that lists all the services offered by a service provider. Returns a list of ProducerMember objects wrapped in ServiceResponse object's responseData variable.
        Parameters:
        request - the ServiceRequest object to be sent
        url - URL that identifies where the message should be sent
        Returns:
        ServiceResponse that holds a list of ProducerMember objects
        Throws:
        SOAPException - if there's a SOAP error
        MalformedURLException - MalformedURLException if no protocol is specified, or an unknown protocol is found, or url is null
